1. <img>, <span>, <a> are inline element tags and do not block other elements from sitting in the same line. 
	But their width cannot be changed.
2. <p>, <div>, etc are blocking elements and do not allow other tags to sit in the same line. Their width can be changed.
3. using inline-block elements we can achieve functionalities of both inline and block elements.
4. display property :-
    a) Block
	b) Inline
	c) Inline-Block
	d) none  --> removes element from the page as if it never existed.
5. visibility: hidden;  --> this is different from display:none such that on using "visibility: hidden;" the
	space of the element is still there on the screen but the element is no more visible.

